<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1058,1409]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Erect or ascending, sparsely branched, to ca 
<quantity box="[657,729,1058,1085]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="25.0">25 cm</quantity>
tall, or to 
<quantity box="[859,931,1058,1085]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="50.0">50 cm</quantity>
long. Shoots homophyllous, densely foliose, almost equally thick throughout, 
<quantity box="[520,630,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10 mm</quantity>
in diam. incl. leaves. Stems tumid, 
<quantity box="[1053,1149,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
thick excl. leaves, almost smooth. Leaves borne in alternating whorls of 6–10, these ca. 
<quantity box="[819,883,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
apart, patent to reflexed, usually strongly recurved, subulate, 4–6 
<emphasis box="[291,310,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[317,453,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.7 mm</quantity>
, subcoriaceous, convex and nitid above, with slightly revolute, entire margins. Leaf bases not or slightly decurrent; sporangia 
<quantity box="[537,651,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1058,1409]" box="[189,644,1238,1264]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1238,1264]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<collectingCountry box="[369,493,1238,1264]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[548,640,1238,1264]" name="Panama" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Panamá</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1058,1409]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,292,1274,1300]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Habitats</emphasis>
:—Terrestrial on banks in montane forest, 
<quantity box="[779,866,1274,1301]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="2350.0">2350 m</quantity>
elev. This species tends to grow in more protected conditions than 
<taxonomicName box="[315,430,1310,1336]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Phlegmariurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reflexus">
<emphasis box="[315,430,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. reflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but at a lower elevation than 
<taxonomicName box="[762,911,1310,1336]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Phlegmariurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hoffmannii">
<emphasis box="[762,911,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. hoffmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
